ce:section.ce:para:
Initially the calculations were performed with PBE functional as shown in the Supplemental Material. From these calculations we detect three peaks for coronene. The peak at 435 nm can be associated to π-π* electronic transitions. In the case of anthracene, there are two main peaks at 530 and 355 nm corresponding to p orbitals transitions because the electron excitation depends on the direction of polarization, while this is not the case for coronene (see supplemental material). However, the values are still far to the transition π-π* observed in the experimental spectra. Consequently, the UV–visible spectra was calculated again using B3LYP functional (Fig. 7
                     ) and compared to the spectra obtained with the PBE functional for coronene and anthracene molecules. PDOS and TDOS curves (Fig. 8
                     ) were calculated to interpret the spectrum behavior. Again, the same peaks obtained with PBE functional are observed, but shifted to lower wavelengths. This change is a consequence of the increase in the band gap between the valence and conduction bands, as can be observed in Fig. 8.
